## OpenAPI refresh (run before API-heavy work)

```bash
mkdir -p api
curl -fsS "{{ base_url }}/openapi.json" -o api/openapi.json
jq -r '
  .paths | to_entries[] as $p
  | $p.value | to_entries[]
  | select((.value.tags // []) | index("{{ role_tag }}"))
  | "\(.key|ascii_upcase)\t\($p.key)\t\(.value.operationId // "-")\t\(.value[\"x-llm-intent\"] // "-")\t\(.value[\"x-when-to-use\"] // [] | join(\" | \"))\t\(.value[\"x-routing-policy\"] // [] | join(\" | \"))"
' api/openapi.json | sort > api/{{ role_tag }}-operations.tsv
```

## API source of truth
- `api/openapi.json`
- `api/{{ role_tag }}-operations.tsv`
  - Columns: METHOD, PATH, OP_ID, X_LLM_INTENT, X_WHEN_TO_USE, X_ROUTING_POLICY

## Shell setup
Run this before any Mission Control API call in a shell:

```bash
export BASE_URL="{{ base_url }}"
export AUTH_TOKEN="{{ auth_token }}"
export AGENT_ID="{{ agent_id }}"
export AGENT_NAME="{{ agent_name }}"
{% if project_id is defined %}
export PROJECT_ID="{{ project_id }}"
{% endif %}
```

Use `curl -fsS` so failed requests stop instead of looking successful.
Always include `-H "X-Agent-Token: $AUTH_TOKEN"`.
For JSON writes, always include `-H "Content-Type: application/json"`.

## Command construction rules
- Do not invent endpoint paths, field names, or HTTP methods.
- First prefer the known-good commands below.
- For anything else, inspect `api/openapi.json` and choose an operation tagged `{{ role_tag }}`.
- Use `PROJECT_ID` as the Mission Control project id for project-scoped agent routes.
- If a command returns 401, stop using the token in memory and re-read `TOOLS.md`; do not retry with old tokens.
- If a command returns 403, you are authenticated but not allowed; ask the lead/user for permission or reassignment.
- If a command returns 422, inspect the response body and OpenAPI schema before retrying.
- Never put `AUTH_TOKEN` in task comments, memory, chat, logs, or screenshots.

## Known-good commands

Preflight health:

```bash
curl -fsS "$BASE_URL/healthz"
```

Heartbeat:

```bash
curl -fsS -X POST "$BASE_URL/api/v1/agent/heartbeat" \
  -H "X-Agent-Token: $AUTH_TOKEN"
```

{% if project_id is defined %}
List active project tasks:

```bash
curl -fsS "$BASE_URL/api/v1/agent/projects/$PROJECT_ID/tasks?status=inbox,in_progress,review" \
  -H "X-Agent-Token: $AUTH_TOKEN"
```

Add a task comment:

```bash
curl -fsS -X POST "$BASE_URL/api/v1/agent/projects/$PROJECT_ID/tasks/<TASK_ID>/comments" \
  -H "X-Agent-Token: $AUTH_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"message":"**Update**\n- ...\n\n**Evidence**\n- ...\n\n**Next**\n- ..."}'
```

Move a task to review with evidence:

```bash
curl -fsS -X PATCH "$BASE_URL/api/v1/agent/projects/$PROJECT_ID/tasks/<TASK_ID>" \
  -H "X-Agent-Token: $AUTH_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"status":"review","comment":"**Update**\n- Ready for review.\n\n**Evidence**\n- ..."}'
```

Ask for the exact task schema before writing unfamiliar fields:

```bash
jq '.components.schemas.TaskUpdate' api/openapi.json
```
